article.description: — Alondes Williams had a career-high 32 points as Wake Forest defeated Western Carolina 87-75 on Friday night.
article.headline: Williams leads Wake Forest over W. Carolina 87-75
article.linkText: Williams leads Wake Forest over W. Carolina 87-75
article.story: WINSTON-SALEM, N.C. -- — Alondes Williams had a career-high 32 points as Wake Forest defeated Western Carolina 87-75 on Friday night. Daivien Williamson had 24 points for Wake Forest (2-0). Cameron Hildreth added 13 points. Jake LaRavia had six steals. Travion McCray had 21 points and six rebounds for the Catamounts (1-1). Tyler Harris added 13 points. Marvin Price had 10 points. Nick Robinson had 9 points and 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25------ Information from: Automated Insights, http://automatedinsights.com/ ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
